column5: We usually go the 2nd week of June but my sister is getting married that weekend so we also will be going up on May 23rd. We got stuck in one of those small 4 man cabins. Going to stick 5 guys in it. I will be in the green 20 foot lund. Pull on up and I will buy you a beer.We caught the trout on Ciscos. Marked quite a few fish in 40 feet of water, dropped the Ciscos down and kind of jigged them around.

Dick,I forgot to mention that we slayed the northern on a lure called the Cisco Kid. My uncle died and left me his fishing equipment and there was an old beatup Kid in there. Works every time. A friend of mine Shawn "the dinger" also has caught a monster with his at Cygnet. Shawn likes to spend a lot of time at the dock, with the Sneakster, when he is not eating.
Looking for anybody that has fished Gooseneck lake on the road west of Minaki towards WhiteDog. Heard that it was good northern fishing, and looking for advice on the lake
fished there today from shore for 2 hours caught one 5 pound laker
Have you fished there before?What part? along the road?
Have you heard if Worth or Sword Lake have opened up yet?
was my first time ever fishing there but not my last.

Dick,We stay at a resort right down the road at Cygnet Lake. Usually we try and get over to Gooseneck at least twice during that week. Once in the morning and once in the evening. The northern are pretty thick up in the weeds. A few nice ones too. Have also got some trout out of there. The ramp sucks!

Turtle,We stay at Cygnet lake also. Going to be there May23rd,when will you be there?how do you catch the trout in this lake,,, i've been there once and caught a few decent 25-32 inch northern and some nice smallies just out from that krappy ramp
